Skybox allows you to explore the behavioral flow of the objects you're tracking in your database.
In this example, we've loaded a small amount of the [GitHub Archive's](http://www.githubarchive.org/) data set.

In this demo you can view what actions GitHub users perform on public, open source projects.
For example, you can step through and see what users do immediately after a repository "push".
Then you can drill down and see what users do after they do a "push" and then "create" a new repository.
You can continue to drill down to any depth since results are computed on the fly.

